{
  "texts": [
    "A zero-CNOT (zCNOT) gate 23 is performed to convert |↑↑⟩ into |↑↓⟩, leaving |↓↓⟩ unchanged.",
    "The construction of the zCNOT gate in this work is shown in Extended Data Fig. 2g.",
    "Ramp to the PSB region for parity readout, and apply a filter that rejects odd-parity states.",
    "(a) If the state is unblockaded and thus determined as |↑↓⟩ or an excited state, the initialization is restarted.",
    "(b) If the state is blockaded and thus determined as |↓↓⟩, the initialization is determined to be completed. 7."
  ]
}